Question-1
Change the query shown so that it displays Nobel prizes for 1950.
Answer-1
SELECT yr, subject, winner FROM nobel WHERE yr = 1950;

Question-2
Show who won the 1962 prize for Literature.
Answer-2
SELECT winner FROM nobel WHERE yr = 1962 AND subject = 'Literature';

Question-3
Show the year and subject that won 'Albert Einstein' his prize.
Answer-3
SELECT yr,subject FROM nobel WHERE winner = 'Albert Einstein';

Question-4
Give the name of the 'Peace' winners since the year 2000, including 2000.
Answer-4
SELECT winner FROM nobel WHERE subject LIKE '%Peace%' AND yr >= 2000;

Question-5
Show all details (yr, subject, winner) of the Literature prize winners for 1980 to 1989 inclusive.
Answer-5
SELECT yr,subject,winner FROM nobel WHERE subject LIKE '%Literature%' AND yr BETWEEN 1980 AND 1989;

Question-6
Show all details of the presidential winners:
Theodore Roosevelt, Woodrow Wilson, Jimmy Carter, Barack Obama
Answer-6
SELECT * FROM nobel WHERE winner IN ('Theodore Roosevelt', 'Woodrow Wilson', 'Jimmy Carter','Barack Obama');

Question-7
Show the winners with first name John
Answer-7
SELECT DISTINCT winner FROM nobel WHERE winner LIKE 'John%';

Question-8
Show the year, subject, and name of Physics winners for 1980 together with the Chemistry winners for 1984.
Answer-8
SELECT * FROM nobel WHERE (subject LIKE '%Physics%' AND yr = 1980) OR (subject LIKE '%chemistry%' AND yr = 1984);

Question-9
Show the year, subject, and name of winners for 1980 excluding Chemistry and Medicine
Answer-9
SELECT * FROM nobel 
WHERE
subject NOT LIKE '%Chemistry%' AND 
subject NOT LIKE '%Medicine%' AND
yr = 1980;

Question-10
Show year, subject, and name of people who won a 'Medicine' prize in an early year (before 1910, not including 1910) together with winners of a 'Literature' prize in a later year (after 2004, including 2004)
Answer-10
SELECT * FROM nobel 
WHERE  
(yr < 1910 AND subject LIKE '%Medicine%')
OR
(yr >=2004 AND subject LIKE '%Literature%');

Question-11
Find all details of the prize won by PETER GRÜNBERG
Answer-11
SELECT * FROM nobel WHERE winner = 'PETER GRÜNBERG';

Question-12
Find all details of the prize won by EUGENE O'NEILL
Answer-12
SELECT * FROM nobel WHERE winner = ('EUGENE O''NEILL');

Question-13
Knights in order
List the winners, year and subject where the winner starts with Sir. Show the the most recent first, then by name order.
Answer-13
SELECT winner, yr, subject FROM nobel WHERE winner LIKE 'Sir%' ORDER BY yr DESC,winner;

Question-14
The expression subject IN ('Chemistry','Physics') can be used as a value - it will be 0 or 1.
Show the 1984 winners and subject ordered by subject and winner name; but list Chemistry and Physics last.
Answer-14
SELECT winner, subject FROM nobel WHERE yr=1984 ORDER BY CASE WHEN Subject IN ('Physics','Chemistry') THEN 1 ELSE 0 END,subject,winner;



